caption: I got a seafood sub tonight.  It probably had a tablespoon of seafood salad on each side of the sun, no lettuce, just a sparse amount of seafood salad!

I used to go to diblasis as a kid and used to love every trip but now I’m not sure what happened but they are very nasty, non professional, and CANT COOK. I asked for my steak and cheese toasted and got it burnt to a crisp and the steak was not cooked good at all so respectfully I went back to just have them make me a new one and the owner Greg was extremely unprofessional mocked me in the store multiple times while I was sitting there waiting for them to cook me another sandwich. When I gave the sandwich to my gf the second time they completely covered it with black pepper so that it is not even edible. I am extremely disappointed and will never return. If I advise do NOT get food here it’s not it.

Fifteen years ago myself and my younger brother spent the summer with dear friends in Everett and every day these two Paddy kids would wander up the block and buy two Philly Cheese steaks with salad and chilli from Di Blasi's . Every time I visit the East Coast I make a pilgrimage to DiBlasi's for a cheese steak. They're so good I'm reviewing them from 3500 miles away, 15 years later and I've every intention of repeating the process again. Thanks for the memories, great food and craic.

The mid 20's girl who takes your order is horrible. She's so rude and disrespectful. If you order from this place you will have to deal with her and you will be disrespected. The food is not worth dealing with such a headache. My experience here is terrible. When I walk in there's the workers friend sitting on the counter like it's a hangout spot and their talking inappropriately. And as I'm leaving the worker throws a attitude very loud demanding me to say thank you and her friend laughs and says to the worker this is her second time talking to customers rudely. As I'm walking out I look back confused to why she was talking to me like that and I happened to see the chefs faces and they looked confused to why their co worker was screaming across the room. I will never ever return to this place. DiBlasi subs need to replace this girl with a new worker with a better attitude if they ever want business again.
